      },
      "date": "2022-09-26 21:50:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHow long ago  was project quota added to ldiskfs?  It might be that  it is  no longer worthwhile  to  check for this in lfs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cc3db712b2958f452d3ce5c018c41a65b0953843",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 655,
        "name": "Arshad Hussain",
        "email": "arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com",
        "username": "arshad512"
      },
      "date": "2022-09-27 05:39:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n>...It might be that  it is  no longer worthwhile  to  check for this in lfs.\nAndreas, late 2.10's (around 2.10.59). With the guard rail check of 2.9.55 we still would not be able to catch the 'lfs project' command support. IMO, this is required unless we change the version check from 2.9.55 to 2.10.58. Please note that there is enough check (change_project() does check and report error if lfs project fails) that is we can remove this check and change_project() will later catch it. But it is good to have the 'lfs project' command check within this function.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c32391b7dd3d2ce7b17f5b21a8728ecee36d93f5",
      "author": {
